org.openimaj.feature.local

Class FloatLocalFeatureAdaptor<L extends Location>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.feature.local.FloatLocalFeatureAdaptor<L>
  • Type Parameters:
    L - The type of Location
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    FeatureVectorProvider<FloatFV>, LocalFeature<L,FloatFV>, LocalFeatureVectorProvider<L,FloatFV>, LocationProvider<L>, org.openimaj.io.Readable, org.openimaj.io.ReadableASCII, org.openimaj.io.ReadableBinary, org.openimaj.io.ReadWriteable, org.openimaj.io.Writeable, org.openimaj.io.WriteableASCII, org.openimaj.io.WriteableBinary

    public class FloatLocalFeatureAdaptor<L extends Location>
extends Object
implements LocalFeature<L,FloatFV>
    This class is designed as a wrapper around any form of local feature and provides a way of exposing that feature as a FloatFV, without the cost of necessarily storing the underlying feature as a FloatFV. For example, this can be used to make a Keypoint look like it's backed by a float array rather than a byte array, without incurring the four-times increase in storage this would incur.

    The implementation also allows a normalisation process to occur during conversion through a Normaliser.

    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
